Package: salvagemap
Version: @VERSION@
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Champlin Guys Data Recovery <champlinguys@gmail.com>
Depends: python3 (>= 3.11),
 python3-pyside6.qtwidgets,
 python3-pyside6.qtgui,
 python3-pyside6.qtcore,
 gddrescue,
 ntfs-3g
Recommends: pkexec | policykit-1, x11-xserver-utils
Homepage: https://github.com/champlinguys/SalvageMap
Description: GUI wrapper over GNU ddrescue with a live sector map
 SalvageMap is a Linux desktop front-end for GNU ddrescue. It renders the
 ddrescue mapfile as a live sector map, drives a targeted recovery workflow
 that images filesystem metadata first and then the most valuable file data,
 and lets you browse the recovered file tree with per-file recovery status.
 .
 It invokes the system ddrescue binary and depends on Qt for Python (PySide6);
 both are pulled in from Ubuntu's own packages. Reading raw block devices needs
 root, so the desktop launcher elevates through pkexec.
